WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:07.207 --> 00:00:08.710
"Progress" is a bad word
around here.

2
00:00:09.577 --> 00:00:11.946
-Clear the road!
-There's a standoff between rez

3
00:00:12.012 --> 00:00:13.581
<i>and truckers trying to get</i>
<i>to that new mine.</i>

4
00:00:13.648 --> 00:00:15.349
All y'all. out of here!

5
00:00:15.415 --> 00:00:16.618
Family name doesn't
carry water anymore.

6
00:00:16.684 --> 00:00:18.385
so you got to hide behind
a federal badge.

7
00:00:20.588 --> 00:00:22.155
These bullets are meant for us.

8
00:00:22.222 --> 00:00:23.858
Shooters are the Clegg brothers.
Carson and Wes.

9
00:00:25.259 --> 00:00:26.493
Move and you're dead!

10
00:00:26.561 --> 00:00:28.095
Life's become
more dangerous for me

11
00:00:28.161 --> 00:00:29.764
since becoming your brother.

12
00:00:29.831 --> 00:00:33.066
<i>I guess being close</i>
<i>to me comes at a cost.</i>

13
00:00:35.000 --> 00:00:41.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

14
00:01:06.801 --> 00:01:08.235
Brought you gifts.

15
00:01:08.302 --> 00:01:10.805
Did you take them
from a fugitive again?

16
00:01:10.872 --> 00:01:14.107
Okay. we got
battery-operated cameras.

17
00:01:14.174 --> 00:01:16.945
motion activated
and night-vision enabled.

18
00:01:17.011 --> 00:01:18.746
I'm my own security system.

19
00:01:18.813 --> 00:01:21.481
And that crack system allowed
somebody to walk up undetected.

20
00:01:21.549 --> 00:01:23.083
drop a shell casing
on your porch.

21
00:01:23.150 --> 00:01:25.653
Hell. I been through worse
than a bullet on my doormat.

22
00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:28.523
Yeah. see. I've come to learn
Montanans don't do theatrics.

23
00:01:28.590 --> 00:01:30.157
You can't ignore this threat.

24
00:01:30.223 --> 00:01:31.626
Well. I sent Tate
to his grandpa's.

25
00:01:31.693 --> 00:01:34.394
and it took you three days
to find this stuff.

26
00:01:34.461 --> 00:01:36.363
It took me a minute
to special-order the right gear

27
00:01:36.430 --> 00:01:37.999
for vengeful Cleggs.

28
00:01:38.800 --> 00:01:41.002
Well. we upset a lot of people
at the standoff.

29
00:01:41.069 --> 00:01:42.570
Could be anybody.

30
00:01:42.637 --> 00:01:44.872
Randall Clegg accosted you
before you killed his son.

31
00:01:44.939 --> 00:01:48.141
I mean. you-you can bet the
field. but my money's on them.

32
00:01:49.409 --> 00:01:51.411
Well. if my past has
proved anything. whoever it is.

33
00:01:51.478 --> 00:01:54.816
they'll come for me.
some way. somehow.

34
00:01:56.149 --> 00:01:58.418
Well. let's be ready.

35
00:02:38.092 --> 00:02:41.495
Whoo! City slicker embarrassed
you at your own sport.

36
00:02:41.562 --> 00:02:44.732
Beginner's luck.

37
00:02:44.799 --> 00:02:47.769
And in my sport.
we don't use a rope.

38
00:02:47.835 --> 00:02:50.505
-I'm a bulldogger.
-A what now?

39
00:02:50.571 --> 00:02:53.675
I jump off a horse and wrestle
a 400-pound steer.

40
00:02:54.509 --> 00:02:56.276
You make a living
suplexing cows?

41
00:02:56.343 --> 00:02:58.211
It's a fair fight.

42
00:02:58.278 --> 00:02:59.747
He comes out of the chute
when I do.

43
00:02:59.814 --> 00:03:01.916
and then another cowboy
called a hazer keeps him

44
00:03:01.983 --> 00:03:03.551
on a path so I can get my angle.

45
00:03:03.618 --> 00:03:05.252
So it sounds like
the hazer does all the work.

46
00:03:05.318 --> 00:03:07.487
and then you get the glory.

47
00:03:07.555 --> 00:03:08.823
I get it.

48
00:03:08.890 --> 00:03:12.359
I feel more like a hazer
than a bulldogger as of late.

49
00:03:12.426 --> 00:03:14.929
Get the fuzzy end
of the lollipop at work?

50
00:03:16.064 --> 00:03:17.732
For now.

51
00:03:17.799 --> 00:03:20.635
But I keep delivering.
making my bosses happy.

52
00:03:20.702 --> 00:03:24.138
they'll send me back
to civilization soon enough.

53
00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:26.774
Okay. Beginner's luck. huh?

54
00:03:47.260 --> 00:03:49.163
What will it be. Henry?

55
00:03:49.229 --> 00:03:51.498
Nose paint. neat. Mads.

56
00:03:55.469 --> 00:03:56.871
You from around here?

57
00:03:57.672 --> 00:03:59.774
You're barking up
the wrong tree. hoss.

58
00:03:59.841 --> 00:04:02.476
No. Sorry. I was just wondering

59
00:04:02.543 --> 00:04:06.279
if you might know
the Clegg family?

60
00:04:06.346 --> 00:04:08.649
Nothing but trouble.

61
00:04:08.716 --> 00:04:09.517
Really?

62
00:04:09.584 --> 00:04:11.953
How much. exactly?

63
00:04:12.019 --> 00:04:14.122
'Cause I might've kicked
a hornet's nest there.

64
00:04:14.188 --> 00:04:18.693
Don't have much use
for rules the rest of us follow.

65
00:04:19.527 --> 00:04:21.662
They making threats?

66
00:04:21.729 --> 00:04:23.330
You know.

67
00:04:25.465 --> 00:04:28.035
Well. you can count on them
to deliver.

68
00:04:37.612 --> 00:04:39.446
What's with the face?

69
00:04:40.782 --> 00:04:42.482
No way Henry was
giving you a hard time.

70
00:04:42.550 --> 00:04:44.484
even though
you probably deserve one.

71
00:04:44.552 --> 00:04:47.755
No. I was just
trying to figure out

72
00:04:47.822 --> 00:04:49.957
how much I got to watch
one of my guy's backs.

73
00:04:51.826 --> 00:04:54.562
You have that math down cold.

74
00:04:54.629 --> 00:04:57.297
Team comes first.
above everything else.

75
00:04:57.364 --> 00:04:59.499
Always has. right?

76
00:05:08.810 --> 00:05:10.211
Miles?

77
00:05:10.278 --> 00:05:12.213
Sabrina. Wow.

78
00:05:12.280 --> 00:05:13.681
Been a while.

79
00:05:13.748 --> 00:05:16.551
You mean since you ghosted me
at our reunion?

80
00:05:16.617 --> 00:05:19.020
Turning your back on the rez
is kind of your thing.

81
00:05:21.022 --> 00:05:22.723
I'm messing with you. dude.

82
00:05:22.790 --> 00:05:25.458
Like I'd dunk on your ambitions
beyond Broken Rock.

83
00:05:25.526 --> 00:05:28.062
College football. Marines. MMA.

84
00:05:28.129 --> 00:05:30.064
I was always cheering you on
from afar.

85
00:05:30.131 --> 00:05:32.432
Ambitions and achievements
are two different things.

86
00:05:32.499 --> 00:05:33.835
So how are you?

87
00:05:33.901 --> 00:05:37.071
Worried there are two of us
at a cowboy bar.

88
00:05:37.138 --> 00:05:38.606
I'm on a date.

89
00:05:38.673 --> 00:05:40.241
What's your excuse?

90
00:05:40.308 --> 00:05:42.475
-Here with my teammates.
-Right.

91
00:05:42.543 --> 00:05:44.078
Heard you're a marshal now.

92
00:05:44.145 --> 00:05:45.847
How's it going?

93
00:05:45.913 --> 00:05:47.682
Traded badges to finally police
for my people.

94
00:05:47.748 --> 00:05:49.984
but some of the elders think

95
00:05:50.051 --> 00:05:52.452
being a marshal
makes me a traitor.

96
00:05:52.520 --> 00:05:54.387
Never were one for fitting in.

97
00:05:54.454 --> 00:05:55.890
But I'm still cheering.

98
00:05:58.626 --> 00:06:01.128
Don't be a stranger. Miles.

99
00:06:10.470 --> 00:06:12.773
How in the hell do we have mayo

100
00:06:12.840 --> 00:06:16.443
that's expired before
this team's even stood up?

101
00:06:16.510 --> 00:06:18.179
Sorry.

102
00:06:18.246 --> 00:06:19.513
I-I swear I'm great at this.

103
00:06:19.580 --> 00:06:21.148
She needs your bulldogger
for inspiration.

104
00:06:21.215 --> 00:06:22.783
Bulldogger?

105
00:06:22.850 --> 00:06:24.484
From "Get me out of Montana"

106
00:06:24.552 --> 00:06:26.988
to rodeo bunny
in the blink of an eye.

107
00:06:27.054 --> 00:06:29.489
You missed the action. Belle.

108
00:06:29.557 --> 00:06:30.825
Yeah. I know.

109
00:06:30.892 --> 00:06:32.425
Movie night
with my kid took priority.

110
00:06:32.492 --> 00:06:34.729
Hey.

111
00:06:34.795 --> 00:06:36.496
How are those cameras
working out?

112
00:06:36.564 --> 00:06:38.065
You ready
to bring your boy home?

113
00:06:38.132 --> 00:06:39.499
I'm gonna give it
a little more time.

114
00:06:39.567 --> 00:06:40.801
So you'd rather hang out

115
00:06:40.868 --> 00:06:42.236
where you were threatened
than with us?

116
00:06:42.303 --> 00:06:44.505
Just trying to keep you
out of the line of fire.

117
00:06:44.572 --> 00:06:46.439
Says the guy
who's gotten us shot at

118
00:06:46.507 --> 00:06:48.342
ever since he showed up.

119
00:06:48.408 --> 00:06:49.710
Harry.

120
00:06:49.777 --> 00:06:51.712
Did we know
that you were coming?

121
00:06:51.779 --> 00:06:54.181
Well. some news is
best delivered in person.

122
00:06:54.248 --> 00:06:56.617
DOJ got a complaint
from Randall Clegg.

123
00:06:56.684 --> 00:06:58.386
Claims you violated
his son's civil rights

124
00:06:58.485 --> 00:07:00.054
when you killed him.

125
00:07:00.121 --> 00:07:01.822
I violated a lot of things.
His rights wasn't one of them.

126
00:07:01.889 --> 00:07:04.892
Well. Clegg claims
that Carson dropped his weapon

127
00:07:04.959 --> 00:07:06.661
before you fired.
so Dutton's in a time-out.

128
00:07:06.727 --> 00:07:09.196
And the rest of you.
get ahead of whatever

129
00:07:09.263 --> 00:07:10.898
the DOJ investigation will find.

130
00:07:10.965 --> 00:07:13.267
Putting our teammate under the
microscope is a waste of time.

131
00:07:13.334 --> 00:07:14.835
Going shields up

132
00:07:14.902 --> 00:07:18.072
for your friend is as admirable
as it is unhelpful.

133
00:07:18.139 --> 00:07:21.208
I need an impartial review.
Deputy Cruz. you're in charge.

134
00:07:25.546 --> 00:07:27.748
Fine. I'll get things started.

135
00:07:27.815 --> 00:07:31.619
Perhaps Carson Clegg dropped
his weapon and you missed it.

136
00:07:31.686 --> 00:07:36.190
I mean. the woods are shadows.
foliage. chaos.

137
00:07:36.257 --> 00:07:37.591
I'm calmest in the chaos.

138
00:07:37.658 --> 00:07:39.193
If he dropped it.
I'd have seen it.

139
00:07:40.493 --> 00:07:41.963
You got any proof?

140
00:07:42.029 --> 00:07:44.065
I got my word.

141
00:07:47.802 --> 00:07:49.704
Good luck
with your investigation.

142
00:07:58.913 --> 00:08:02.016
Hey. you know
those claims don't have legs.

143
00:08:02.083 --> 00:08:04.085
Don't need any
with Gifford propping them up.

144
00:08:04.151 --> 00:08:05.953
I'm not waiting around
to learn my fate.

145
00:08:06.020 --> 00:08:08.022
No. you're not. You're actually
rolling out with me.

146
00:08:08.089 --> 00:08:09.690
'cause the Forest Service
needs bodies to help

147
00:08:09.757 --> 00:08:11.926
with a search and rescue
up at Bridger Range.

148
00:08:11.993 --> 00:08:13.794
and I'm betting
you know the area.

149
00:08:13.861 --> 00:08:16.496
Yeah. it's a brutal group
of steep peaks.

150
00:08:16.564 --> 00:08:19.834
Well. you up
for some man versus nature?

151
00:08:20.668 --> 00:08:22.803
Safer than what I'm facing here.

152
00:08:29.043 --> 00:08:31.112
<i>Helicopter carrying Tom Weaver</i>

153
00:08:31.178 --> 00:08:33.581
<i>and his pilot called in an</i>
<i>SOS after the wind kicked up.</i>

154
00:08:33.647 --> 00:08:35.716
We're still trying to locate it.

155
00:08:35.783 --> 00:08:37.385
You don't have eyes from above?

156
00:08:37.451 --> 00:08:40.187
The wind up there is a no go
for air assets. even unmanned.

157
00:08:40.254 --> 00:08:41.856
Leaves us with over
a thousand square miles

158
00:08:41.922 --> 00:08:43.691
to cover on foot and a shortage

159
00:08:43.758 --> 00:08:45.493
of search-and-rescue-qualified
Rangers.

160
00:08:45.559 --> 00:08:48.662
You two will be
handling section D4.

161
00:08:48.729 --> 00:08:50.031
Sorry to interrupt.

162
00:08:50.097 --> 00:08:52.733
Are there any updates
on my father?

163
00:08:55.202 --> 00:08:58.239
Elevation's over 8.500 feet
up there.

164
00:08:58.305 --> 00:08:59.740
Get ready for some climbing.

165
00:08:59.807 --> 00:09:01.510
Please.
I'm a damn mountain goat.

166
00:09:01.575 --> 00:09:04.345
Just try and keep up. bro.

167
00:09:05.146 --> 00:09:07.281
Be nice to get Dolly Weaver
some answers about her dad.

168
00:09:07.348 --> 00:09:10.051
Weather's only gonna get worse.
so shove off.

169
00:09:10.117 --> 00:09:11.786
We're armed. but thank you.

170
00:09:11.852 --> 00:09:15.122
Your standard issue can't handle
what's on that mountain.

171
00:09:23.898 --> 00:09:25.366
Is this what

172
00:09:25.433 --> 00:09:28.235
you being hard at work
on the investigation looks like?

173
00:09:28.302 --> 00:09:29.737
Good food's in the good kitchen.

174
00:09:29.804 --> 00:09:32.139
and we've worked up
quite an appetite already.

175
00:09:33.240 --> 00:09:35.643
Okay. so. Miles said
he didn't see anything

176
00:09:35.709 --> 00:09:37.411
because he was engaged
with Wes Clegg.

177
00:09:37.478 --> 00:09:40.515
and there are no red flags
in Kayce's incident report.

178
00:09:40.581 --> 00:09:43.484
Well. you trust a Dutton's word
at your own peril.

179
00:09:43.552 --> 00:09:46.220
Okay. It's not like
Kayce is some dirty beat cop.

180
00:09:46.287 --> 00:09:47.855
So why have you decided
he's guilty?

181
00:09:47.922 --> 00:09:49.256
It's not about guilt.

182
00:09:49.323 --> 00:09:51.092
If he's here
with his own personal agenda.

183
00:09:51.158 --> 00:09:53.094
how effective can this team be?

184
00:09:53.894 --> 00:09:55.729
And Dutton dragging
this team down is gonna be

185
00:09:55.796 --> 00:09:58.533
that much harder for you
to get reassigned to D.C.

186
00:09:58.599 --> 00:10:00.101
It's in your best interest

187
00:10:00.167 --> 00:10:02.369
to be very thorough
in this investigation.

188
00:10:02.436 --> 00:10:03.838
Are you telling me

189
00:10:03.904 --> 00:10:05.940
to manufacture evidence
to support Clegg's claim?

190
00:10:06.006 --> 00:10:09.977
I'm saying that even if there's
no smoke behind this Clegg fire.

191
00:10:10.044 --> 00:10:12.514
DOJ investigation's gonna find
other Dutton skeletons

192
00:10:12.581 --> 00:10:13.848
that can hurt this team.

193
00:10:13.914 --> 00:10:15.749
Best we find them ourselves.

194
00:10:15.816 --> 00:10:18.886
or get buried
when someone else does.

195
00:10:18.953 --> 00:10:20.654
You want to get out
of this ditch

196
00:10:20.721 --> 00:10:23.858
that your old team
threw you in? Hmm?

197
00:10:24.658 --> 00:10:27.562
You better get your hands dirty.

198
00:10:32.199 --> 00:10:35.970
Didn't become a marshal
to snoop on my teammates.

199
00:10:36.036 --> 00:10:38.105
Feels especially wrong
digging into a guy

200
00:10:38.172 --> 00:10:40.641
who keeps pulling our asses
out of the fire.

201
00:10:40.708 --> 00:10:42.276
This investigation's a great way

202
00:10:42.343 --> 00:10:46.280
for Gifford to destroy any trust
that we've built with Kayce.

203
00:10:46.347 --> 00:10:49.183
Clegg's fronting for sure. but
Gifford's right about one thing.

204
00:10:49.250 --> 00:10:51.385
The complaint will impact
the rest of the team.

205
00:10:51.452 --> 00:10:54.255
So. I called a friend at DOJ
from law school--

206
00:10:54.321 --> 00:10:55.823
You're a lawyer?

207
00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:57.858
That's even less believable
than you having a friend.

208
00:10:57.925 --> 00:11:00.294
Okay. I said
I went to law school.

209
00:11:00.361 --> 00:11:01.929
I didn't say I finished.

210
00:11:01.996 --> 00:11:04.965
My friend said Clegg had a local
attorney file the complaint.

211
00:11:05.032 --> 00:11:07.201
Um. an Andrew Schroeder.

212
00:11:08.503 --> 00:11:10.539
Guy has a track record of filing

213
00:11:10.605 --> 00:11:12.339
civil suits
against law enforcement.

214
00:11:12.406 --> 00:11:15.644
Huh.
Well. DOJ finding against Kayce

215
00:11:15.709 --> 00:11:17.144
would set up Clegg to sue him.

216
00:11:17.211 --> 00:11:20.881
Unless we can prove
that Carson Clegg was armed

217
00:11:20.948 --> 00:11:22.883
when he was killed.

218
00:11:24.018 --> 00:11:26.555
Sheriff's office
finish processing the site?

219
00:11:26.621 --> 00:11:29.390
Bullets fired from the Cleggs'
positions came from two weapons.

220
00:11:29.456 --> 00:11:31.992
So both men were armed.
Case closed.

221
00:11:32.059 --> 00:11:35.362
One gun was recovered from Wes.
Haven't found Carson's.

222
00:11:35.429 --> 00:11:37.198
The man fell down a damn ravine.

223
00:11:37.264 --> 00:11:38.832
The gun's probably
floating downriver.

224
00:11:38.899 --> 00:11:41.302
They know that property
better than anyone.

225
00:11:41.368 --> 00:11:45.005
Maybe they got to it
before law enforcement could.

226
00:11:45.072 --> 00:11:48.209
No gun makes clearing Kayce
even more complicated.

227
00:11:51.212 --> 00:11:53.548
I know Schroeder.

228
00:11:53.615 --> 00:11:58.252
Let me go remind him that
his new client is an outlaw.

229
00:11:58.319 --> 00:11:59.420
We should also sniff out

230
00:11:59.486 --> 00:12:02.256
if he's got any evidence
he's holding back.

231
00:12:02.323 --> 00:12:03.857
We?

232
00:12:12.634 --> 00:12:14.201
So. is the. uh. quiet man act

233
00:12:14.268 --> 00:12:15.836
'cause you're taking in
the scenery.

234
00:12:15.903 --> 00:12:18.439
or you plotting your revenge
against Clegg?

235
00:12:18.506 --> 00:12:21.610
I'm just glad he's coming
after my badge and not my kid.

236
00:12:21.676 --> 00:12:24.211
Well. Gifford's way out of line
backing up a bogus claim. man.

237
00:12:24.278 --> 00:12:27.848
He's just taking out
some old beef with my dad on me.

238
00:12:27.915 --> 00:12:29.416
So's Clegg.

239
00:12:29.483 --> 00:12:31.085
Not the first time
I've been punished

240
00:12:31.151 --> 00:12:33.387
for doing
what I thought was right.

241
00:12:33.454 --> 00:12:35.222
When was that?

242
00:12:36.090 --> 00:12:38.092
Pretty much since birth.

243
00:12:39.527 --> 00:12:41.962
-You smell that?
-Mm-hmm.

244
00:12:42.029 --> 00:12:43.397
Aviation fuel.

245
00:12:43.464 --> 00:12:46.233
Nothing brings me back
to Afghanistan faster.

246
00:12:46.300 --> 00:12:47.768
Come on.

247
00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:00.981
Whoa.

248
00:13:09.323 --> 00:13:13.160
I'm not sure Tom Weaver deserves
us risking our lives for him.

249
00:13:13.227 --> 00:13:15.697
Oh. I didn't realize
that you knew him.

250
00:13:15.764 --> 00:13:17.898
Of him. He's a transplant.

251
00:13:17.965 --> 00:13:19.300
Bought a big chunk of land

252
00:13:19.366 --> 00:13:21.268
and thinks that makes him
king of the valley.

253
00:13:21.335 --> 00:13:23.037
Oh. I see. You don't like him

254
00:13:23.103 --> 00:13:25.139
'cause he's doing a bad
impression of your dad. huh?

255
00:13:25.205 --> 00:13:27.241
Or a good one. Flying around

256
00:13:27.308 --> 00:13:29.276
in these conditions.
knowing a storm's coming in?

257
00:13:29.343 --> 00:13:31.278
These ranchers get obsessed
with their brands.

258
00:13:31.345 --> 00:13:33.581
start treating their people
like livestock.

259
00:13:35.082 --> 00:13:36.917
There's a sheen on the water.

260
00:13:40.354 --> 00:13:42.222
-Bird went down upstream.
-Mm-hmm.

261
00:13:55.469 --> 00:13:57.938
So how do you know
this fancy lawyer?

262
00:13:58.005 --> 00:13:59.741
Your husband his dentist?

263
00:13:59.808 --> 00:14:01.342
His wife queen of the PTA?

264
00:14:01.408 --> 00:14:03.243
You do couple's Pilates
together?

265
00:14:03.310 --> 00:14:06.548
Don't embarrass me
in front of him.

266
00:14:06.614 --> 00:14:08.616
Oh. why? Because he'd spread
the word at the country club?

267
00:14:11.385 --> 00:14:13.153
Look at that shine. Terry.

268
00:14:13.220 --> 00:14:15.489
It's like a Yogo sapphire.

269
00:14:15.557 --> 00:14:19.326
Well. you do love
reflective surfaces.

270
00:14:20.361 --> 00:14:21.495
Andrew.

271
00:14:21.563 --> 00:14:23.163
Belle.

272
00:14:23.230 --> 00:14:26.467
I haven't seen you since your
birdie on 18 cleaned me out.

273
00:14:26.534 --> 00:14:27.935
Damn straight.

274
00:14:28.001 --> 00:14:30.871
You here. uh.
looking for a gift for Jared?

275
00:14:30.938 --> 00:14:32.674
I'm looking out for you.

276
00:14:33.508 --> 00:14:36.310
This is my colleague.
Andrea Cruz.

277
00:14:37.111 --> 00:14:39.880
Andrew. we hear you filed
a civil rights complaint

278
00:14:39.947 --> 00:14:41.415
against our teammate.

279
00:14:42.216 --> 00:14:44.719
You've heard of privilege.

280
00:14:44.786 --> 00:14:46.654
I can't talk about my clients.

281
00:14:47.689 --> 00:14:50.859
Well. given our relationship.

282
00:14:50.924 --> 00:14:54.428
I wanted to share that the
Cleggs are facing investigations

283
00:14:54.495 --> 00:14:56.897
on the local.
state and federal level.

284
00:14:56.964 --> 00:14:58.365
How would the club feel

285
00:14:58.432 --> 00:15:01.603
about you being associated
with such lowlifes?

286
00:15:02.637 --> 00:15:04.572
Andrew. business can't be so bad

287
00:15:04.639 --> 00:15:07.809
that you have to advocate
for actual...

288
00:15:07.876 --> 00:15:09.309
criminals.

289
00:15:09.376 --> 00:15:11.211
Marshals should be
more concerned about

290
00:15:11.278 --> 00:15:13.213
the actual criminal
carrying their badge.

291
00:15:15.282 --> 00:15:17.284
Kayce is a chip off
the John Dutton block.

292
00:15:17.351 --> 00:15:21.255
thinking he can play
outside the lines.

293
00:15:22.055 --> 00:15:24.224
This'll do double duty:

294
00:15:24.291 --> 00:15:28.630
Carson's funeral
and talking to the press.

295
00:15:30.532 --> 00:15:33.267
Making noise to the media
will influence the DOJ's review

296
00:15:33.333 --> 00:15:34.935
of the complaint against Kayce.

297
00:15:35.002 --> 00:15:39.641
Everyone in Montana will cheer
when a Dutton finally learns

298
00:15:39.707 --> 00:15:43.076
a badge isn't a shield
for their sins.

299
00:15:43.143 --> 00:15:46.113
Okay. so you can prove
that Carson was unarmed

300
00:15:46.180 --> 00:15:47.816
when Kayce killed him?

301
00:15:47.882 --> 00:15:49.517
Can you prove he wasn't?

302
00:15:59.761 --> 00:16:02.329
Schroeder is gonna focus
on Kayce's character

303
00:16:02.396 --> 00:16:05.165
and make him out to look like
a cowboy who ignores the rules.

304
00:16:05.232 --> 00:16:07.067
Then we need to look
into his Navy service.

305
00:16:07.134 --> 00:16:08.469
his life in Montana.

306
00:16:08.536 --> 00:16:11.271
find out
who our teammate really is.

307
00:16:11.338 --> 00:16:13.474
Well. seems like a good time

308
00:16:13.541 --> 00:16:17.779
to remind you that killing Clegg
was justified.

309
00:16:17.846 --> 00:16:20.849
"Justified" and "right"
aren't always the same thing.

310
00:16:20.915 --> 00:16:24.786
So. what? You're... you're
a bad man for doing your job?

311
00:16:24.853 --> 00:16:28.590
There's only one person ever
believed me to be a good man.

312
00:16:28.656 --> 00:16:31.024
She's gone.

313
00:16:31.091 --> 00:16:33.862
Your teammates believe
in you. Coyo.

314
00:16:33.928 --> 00:16:35.530
Well. they're investigating me.

315
00:16:35.597 --> 00:16:38.566
I know they have to.
but when the people

316
00:16:38.633 --> 00:16:40.535
you expect to have your back
are trying to punish you.

317
00:16:40.602 --> 00:16:42.704
-well. it tells you something.
-So. what?

318
00:16:42.770 --> 00:16:45.205
You're fine
losing the badge. then?

319
00:16:46.373 --> 00:16:48.075
Whatever happens happens.

320
00:16:48.141 --> 00:16:49.677
It's kind of hard
for your teammates

321
00:16:49.744 --> 00:16:51.011
to get close to you. man.

322
00:16:51.078 --> 00:16:53.113
if you always keep them
at arm's length.

323
00:16:53.180 --> 00:16:54.849
Just 'cause I won't go
to the bar with them

324
00:16:54.916 --> 00:16:57.417
doesn't mean I wouldn't jump
into the fire for them.

325
00:16:58.887 --> 00:17:00.220
Hey.

326
00:17:01.021 --> 00:17:02.356
Eyes on the crash site.

327
00:17:02.422 --> 00:17:05.058
Mm-hmm. That's it. Let's go.

328
00:17:15.570 --> 00:17:17.539
That's far enough.

329
00:17:21.676 --> 00:17:23.210
Dismount and eat dirt.

330
00:17:25.312 --> 00:17:27.682
I just need
whatever supplies you have.

331
00:17:34.022 --> 00:17:35.389
Hey. you haven't. uh.

332
00:17:35.455 --> 00:17:38.058
seen a crashed helo
around here. have you?

333
00:17:38.826 --> 00:17:41.896
That badge.
The hell are Feds doing up here?

334
00:17:41.963 --> 00:17:44.197
It's got nothing
to do with you. okay?

335
00:17:44.264 --> 00:17:45.700
You should really put
that gun down

336
00:17:45.767 --> 00:17:48.435
before you get yourself
into some real trouble.

337
00:17:49.604 --> 00:17:51.138
Hey. look at me.

338
00:17:51.204 --> 00:17:53.206
No. no. no.
come here. look at me.

339
00:17:53.273 --> 00:17:57.210
Hey. you shoot one of us. man.
the other one's gonna kill you.

340
00:17:57.277 --> 00:17:59.079
You got it?

341
00:18:07.321 --> 00:18:09.691
Picked the wrong wagon train
to ambush.

342
00:18:11.859 --> 00:18:14.929
All right. All right.

343
00:18:14.996 --> 00:18:17.297
Wasn't gonna hurt anyone.

344
00:18:17.932 --> 00:18:19.499
Okay?

345
00:18:19.567 --> 00:18:22.637
What are you doing
living all the way up here. huh?

346
00:18:23.437 --> 00:18:25.807
Got laid off.

347
00:18:25.873 --> 00:18:27.909
Wife left. lost my house.

348
00:18:27.976 --> 00:18:30.310
I live off the land.
or I don't live at all.

349
00:18:31.445 --> 00:18:33.982
Hmm. What you want
to do with him?

350
00:18:34.048 --> 00:18:36.551
We can zip-tie him to a tree

351
00:18:36.618 --> 00:18:38.987
and just pick him up
on the way down?

352
00:18:39.053 --> 00:18:40.521
Oh.

353
00:18:40.588 --> 00:18:44.157
Be a death sentence if the storm
gets him before we do.

354
00:18:45.093 --> 00:18:46.193
Yeah.

355
00:18:46.259 --> 00:18:47.862
All right. look.

356
00:18:47.929 --> 00:18:50.064
You're gonna head down
to the ranger station.

357
00:18:50.130 --> 00:18:51.899
and you're gonna
turn yourself in.

358
00:18:54.569 --> 00:18:56.370
Yes. sir.

359
00:19:00.108 --> 00:19:01.676
Go!

360
00:19:05.178 --> 00:19:06.714
You think he'll surrender?

361
00:19:06.781 --> 00:19:09.316
I wouldn't.

362
00:19:12.920 --> 00:19:14.789
Come on.

363
00:19:16.356 --> 00:19:18.626
It feels wrong
letting that guy go.

364
00:19:18.693 --> 00:19:20.662
He lives
by the laws of nature now.

365
00:19:20.728 --> 00:19:21.896
Survive or die.

366
00:19:21.963 --> 00:19:24.398
Kind of envy
the lack of gray area out here.

367
00:19:24.464 --> 00:19:26.266
Mm.

368
00:19:27.367 --> 00:19:30.337
False summit. Son of a bitch.

369
00:19:30.404 --> 00:19:32.439
Going around takes time
we don't have.

370
00:19:32.507 --> 00:19:34.809
Only option's straight up.

371
00:19:34.876 --> 00:19:37.879
Well. vertical climb means
travel light. travel fast.

372
00:19:37.945 --> 00:19:39.212
so essential gear only.

373
00:19:40.915 --> 00:19:42.482
Come on.

374
00:19:51.258 --> 00:19:52.827
All Kayce's deployments.

375
00:19:52.894 --> 00:19:56.097
No court-martials.
no captain's masts.

376
00:19:56.164 --> 00:19:58.365
He's basically a model sailor.

377
00:19:58.432 --> 00:20:00.601
With a Silver Star to prove it.

378
00:20:00.668 --> 00:20:04.138
Good luck to Clegg trying to
paint a war hero in a bad light.

379
00:20:04.204 --> 00:20:05.840
Well. Cal's mentioned

380
00:20:05.907 --> 00:20:09.242
that he and other
special operators struggled

381
00:20:09.309 --> 00:20:11.411
to turn off the switch
when they got out.

382
00:20:11.478 --> 00:20:13.480
"Cal's mentioned." huh?

383
00:20:13.548 --> 00:20:15.783
Rather intimate
personal history.

384
00:20:15.850 --> 00:20:20.021
Yes. sweet Andrea.
I am befriending my coworkers

385
00:20:20.088 --> 00:20:21.856
'cause I don't have
one foot out the door.

386
00:20:21.923 --> 00:20:23.691
The point is. SEALs--

387
00:20:23.758 --> 00:20:25.593
they don't have
the best reputation.

388
00:20:25.660 --> 00:20:29.262
so it could open Kayce up to be
painted as a rogue warrior.

389
00:20:31.966 --> 00:20:35.268
Few years back.
the militia kidnapped his son.

390
00:20:35.335 --> 00:20:37.437
Word on the rez was

391
00:20:37.505 --> 00:20:39.473
Kayce took a bunch
of ranch hands.

392
00:20:39.540 --> 00:20:40.875
led an assault to get him back.

393
00:20:40.942 --> 00:20:44.078
He took on a militia
with his cowboy buddies?

394
00:20:44.145 --> 00:20:46.581
Was it extrajudicial?

395
00:20:46.647 --> 00:20:48.850
His dad was
the livestock commissioner.

396
00:20:48.916 --> 00:20:51.418
Kayce was his deputy.

397
00:20:51.485 --> 00:20:53.788
Maybe they did it
through their office.

398
00:20:53.855 --> 00:20:56.090
That's called frontier justice.

399
00:20:56.157 --> 00:20:58.893
So Clegg may have a point.

400
00:21:08.970 --> 00:21:10.638
Cal. over here.

401
00:21:29.524 --> 00:21:31.559
Please help her.

402
00:21:34.762 --> 00:21:37.732
Weak pulse.
She's barely breathing.

403
00:21:37.799 --> 00:21:39.267
Hey. are you Tom Weaver?

404
00:21:39.332 --> 00:21:41.002
Yeah.

405
00:21:41.068 --> 00:21:42.970
Well. we are U.S. Marshals. and
we're here to help you. okay?

406
00:21:43.037 --> 00:21:44.471
You got a sitrep?

407
00:21:44.539 --> 00:21:46.707
We get her off this thing.
her guts stay with it.

408
00:21:47.909 --> 00:21:49.744
All right. let's find a spot
to cut it from the tree.

409
00:21:49.811 --> 00:21:51.411
We'll just move it with her.

410
00:21:51.478 --> 00:21:53.881
Service Base.
we have the downed helo.

411
00:21:53.948 --> 00:21:55.783
and we got two survivors
in section D4.

412
00:21:55.850 --> 00:21:57.785
We're gonna need
an immediate CASEVAC.

413
00:21:57.852 --> 00:21:59.754
Repeat. an immediate CASEVAC.

414
00:21:59.821 --> 00:22:02.056
<i>Negative.</i>
<i>All flights are grounded.</i>

415
00:22:02.123 --> 00:22:03.825
<i>Weather conditions</i>
<i>are worsening.</i>

416
00:22:03.891 --> 00:22:06.359
Anything we have to cut her off
is with the horses.

417
00:22:06.426 --> 00:22:07.829
I'll be back in ten mikes.

418
00:22:07.895 --> 00:22:10.330
I'm sensing
you boys were military?

419
00:22:10.397 --> 00:22:11.732
Navy.

420
00:22:11.799 --> 00:22:16.604
My pilot. Helen.
she's a vet. too.

421
00:22:17.404 --> 00:22:19.841
Go. I'm-a stabilize Helen. okay?

422
00:22:33.221 --> 00:22:34.589
Easy.

423
00:22:38.960 --> 00:22:41.095
I didn't survive the war on
terror to be killed by a bear.

424
00:22:41.162 --> 00:22:42.930
Shotgun we left on the horse
would've helped.

425
00:22:44.899 --> 00:22:46.767
Pistols are just gonna
piss it off.

426
00:22:55.408 --> 00:22:57.044
Well. this is no good
for the pilot.

427
00:23:12.159 --> 00:23:14.161
Bear bugged out. for now.

428
00:23:14.228 --> 00:23:16.429
It didn't help. though. that
it was shaking the damn thing.

429
00:23:16.496 --> 00:23:18.733
Helen's dead.

430
00:23:22.870 --> 00:23:25.840
Why'd you make her fly
in these conditions?

431
00:23:25.907 --> 00:23:28.709
Extreme winds weren't
on any weather report.

432
00:23:28.776 --> 00:23:32.546
I'm on the clock purchasing land
over in Springhill.

433
00:23:32.613 --> 00:23:34.949
I needed to assess
the rock cover.

434
00:23:35.016 --> 00:23:38.152
Yeah? Did you get a good look
at it from the back seat?

435
00:23:38.219 --> 00:23:40.821
Helen thought
if we rebalanced the weight.

436
00:23:40.888 --> 00:23:42.823
it would help
the chopper get under control

437
00:23:42.890 --> 00:23:45.126
-when the winds kicked up.
-Well. she saved your life.

438
00:23:45.192 --> 00:23:47.460
even though you valued
your ranch more than hers.

439
00:23:47.528 --> 00:23:49.196
Hey. look.
we got to cut him loose.

440
00:23:49.263 --> 00:23:51.165
Okay?

441
00:23:51.232 --> 00:23:52.667
Yeah.

442
00:23:52.733 --> 00:23:54.802
Rotary saw or a Broco torch
here would be nice.

443
00:23:54.869 --> 00:23:56.771
If we knock out this seat.
we can probably pull him free.

444
00:23:56.837 --> 00:23:58.773
but we might break his leg
in the process.

445
00:23:58.839 --> 00:24:00.741
Go ahead.
I'm sensing you'll enjoy it.

446
00:24:00.808 --> 00:24:02.743
Yeah. well. the extraction strap

447
00:24:02.810 --> 00:24:04.345
is not gonna work
with a broken femur.

448
00:24:04.412 --> 00:24:06.446
And I can't bust you up any more

449
00:24:06.514 --> 00:24:08.448
without a plan
down this mountain.

450
00:24:08.516 --> 00:24:10.584
You have
to take Helen down. too.

451
00:24:10.651 --> 00:24:11.953
Rescue mission takes priority.

452
00:24:12.019 --> 00:24:14.155
Recovery team will get her
later. okay?

453
00:24:14.221 --> 00:24:16.724
Can you grab her wedding ring?

454
00:24:16.791 --> 00:24:21.195
Prefer her husband gets it
from me than a stranger.

455
00:24:23.698 --> 00:24:26.600
Hey. suggestion box
is open. Coyo.

456
00:24:27.568 --> 00:24:29.904
Well. since we're already
taking the seat out.

457
00:24:29.971 --> 00:24:32.239
we can use that to stabilize
his leg while we belay down.

458
00:24:32.306 --> 00:24:34.542
One of us tandems.
the other one uses the horse

459
00:24:34.608 --> 00:24:35.843
to handle the extra weight.

460
00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:37.678
Horse-assisted tandem belay.

461
00:24:37.745 --> 00:24:39.180
Okay. Missed that day in BUD/S.

462
00:24:39.246 --> 00:24:43.351
Wait. A cowboy. a SEAL
and a U.S. Marshal?

463
00:24:43.417 --> 00:24:45.119
He's also a member
of the first family

464
00:24:45.186 --> 00:24:46.454
of Montana ranchers.

465
00:24:46.554 --> 00:24:48.756
Wait. You're a Dutton?

466
00:24:48.823 --> 00:24:50.291
Yeah. Bite down on this.

467
00:24:50.358 --> 00:24:51.993
Ready?

468
00:24:52.059 --> 00:24:54.095
One. two. three.

469
00:25:02.103 --> 00:25:04.038
So. what has my crack team
learned?

470
00:25:04.105 --> 00:25:07.808
Well. it's a "he said. he said"
about whether or not

471
00:25:07.875 --> 00:25:10.478
Carson Clegg was armed
when Kayce shot him.

472
00:25:10.544 --> 00:25:12.313
That's precisely why
I tasked you

473
00:25:12.380 --> 00:25:13.914
with finding Kayce's skeletons.

474
00:25:13.981 --> 00:25:17.084
Deputy Cruz.
what's in his closet?

475
00:25:17.151 --> 00:25:21.522
Circumstances surrounding his
son's kidnapping recovery are...

476
00:25:21.589 --> 00:25:23.190
sketchy.

477
00:25:23.257 --> 00:25:25.926
Sketchy?

478
00:25:25.993 --> 00:25:27.128
How?

479
00:25:28.229 --> 00:25:33.067
It may be a case
of frontier justice.

480
00:25:33.134 --> 00:25:36.103
John Dutton
was livestock commissioner.

481
00:25:36.170 --> 00:25:38.105
and he resigned
a few weeks after.

482
00:25:38.172 --> 00:25:40.241
Giving up power is close
as a confession

483
00:25:40.307 --> 00:25:41.709
as a Dutton's capable of.

484
00:25:41.776 --> 00:25:43.110
I mean. could this be
more frontier justice?

485
00:25:43.177 --> 00:25:46.047
Did Kayce have a reason
to kill Clegg?

486
00:25:46.113 --> 00:25:48.049
Other than defending
his own life?

487
00:25:48.115 --> 00:25:49.884
Well. maybe he thought
Carson had something to do

488
00:25:49.950 --> 00:25:51.352
with his father's death
or his brother's disappearance.

489
00:25:51.419 --> 00:25:52.887
Randall Clegg was a pain
in the ass for John Dutton

490
00:25:52.953 --> 00:25:55.423
when he was
livestock commissioner.

491
00:25:55.489 --> 00:25:57.458
but that's a weak motive.

492
00:25:57.526 --> 00:25:59.460
He left a trail of bodies

493
00:25:59.528 --> 00:26:00.828
after his buddy
Chairman Rainwater

494
00:26:00.895 --> 00:26:03.030
was almost killed. didn't he?

495
00:26:03.097 --> 00:26:04.665
All justified.

496
00:26:10.104 --> 00:26:13.140
Did... Kayce have a connection

497
00:26:13.207 --> 00:26:14.942
to the Broken Rock man
the Cleggs shot?

498
00:26:15.009 --> 00:26:17.244
- Ernie Cano?
- Yeah.

499
00:26:17.311 --> 00:26:19.947
I'm not a human LinkedIn
for the rez. you know.

500
00:26:22.817 --> 00:26:25.219
Let's you and I take a drive.

501
00:26:29.490 --> 00:26:32.593
- I'll solo down. prep the horse.
- Yeah.

502
00:26:32.660 --> 00:26:34.195
Altitude's getting to me. man.

503
00:26:34.261 --> 00:26:35.830
I think it's gonna be safer
if you tandem with Weaver.

504
00:26:35.896 --> 00:26:37.298
The only guy who never puked

505
00:26:37.364 --> 00:26:38.999
in the Hindu Kush
can't handle Montana?

506
00:26:39.066 --> 00:26:41.702
I'm gonna find some branches.
stabilize his leg.

507
00:26:41.769 --> 00:26:44.705
You just tend to his wounds.
all right?

508
00:26:50.711 --> 00:26:52.379
Sorry about your father.

509
00:26:54.115 --> 00:26:57.051
I got to Montana too late
to meet him.

510
00:26:57.118 --> 00:26:59.854
but from the stories.
it seems like

511
00:26:59.920 --> 00:27:02.656
he could've taught me
a thing or two about ranching.

512
00:27:03.457 --> 00:27:05.860
Wasn't much for teaching.

513
00:27:05.926 --> 00:27:07.862
You had to learn the hard way
with him.

514
00:27:07.928 --> 00:27:10.798
Yeah. My old man
was a hard-ass. too.

515
00:27:10.865 --> 00:27:12.633
only on Wall Street.

516
00:27:14.835 --> 00:27:16.103
Working for him made me rich.

517
00:27:16.170 --> 00:27:19.373
but I was never too fond
of his shadow.

518
00:27:21.876 --> 00:27:24.478
Part of coming out here
was to escape it.

519
00:27:24.546 --> 00:27:26.180
Good luck.

520
00:27:26.247 --> 00:27:29.717
Trying to escape my dad's shadow
just led me into more darkness.

521
00:27:29.783 --> 00:27:31.620
Yeah. we don't get
to pick our fathers.

522
00:27:31.685 --> 00:27:36.023
No. but you wanting to tell
her husband yourself reminded me

523
00:27:36.090 --> 00:27:37.592
of a good thing mine once did.

524
00:27:37.658 --> 00:27:39.093
Well. I don't think

525
00:27:39.160 --> 00:27:41.428
I'll remind you of him
as a rancher.

526
00:27:41.495 --> 00:27:43.497
It's a hard living.

527
00:27:43.565 --> 00:27:46.800
You got to be all in
to have a hope of success.

528
00:27:46.867 --> 00:27:50.738
I cut my teeth
on my grandparents' ranch

529
00:27:50.804 --> 00:27:53.707
in Wyoming as a kid.

530
00:27:53.774 --> 00:27:56.210
Thought I'd...

531
00:27:56.277 --> 00:27:58.245
try and build something
of my own.

532
00:27:58.312 --> 00:28:01.081
leave my family something
more than a stock portfolio.

533
00:28:03.450 --> 00:28:05.319
Hearing a crackerjack like you

534
00:28:05.386 --> 00:28:07.755
quit the cattle game
giving me pause. though.

535
00:28:07.821 --> 00:28:10.559
I'm not all out.
Still got 300 pairs.

536
00:28:10.625 --> 00:28:13.093
How do you have time for that?

537
00:28:13.160 --> 00:28:15.530
Hey. Storm's getting close.

538
00:28:15.597 --> 00:28:18.132
so let's build this and boogie.

539
00:28:20.602 --> 00:28:21.936
These are my neighbors.

540
00:28:22.002 --> 00:28:24.805
I have to be able
to face them when I go home.

541
00:28:27.542 --> 00:28:30.044
Is this Ernie Cano's room?

542
00:28:30.110 --> 00:28:31.680
Miles. wh-what's going on?

543
00:28:31.745 --> 00:28:33.948
Excuse me. Auntie.

544
00:28:34.014 --> 00:28:36.150
Marshal Gifford here would like
to speak with Ernie.

545
00:28:36.217 --> 00:28:39.220
Ernie's down in PT for his leg.

546
00:28:39.286 --> 00:28:41.889
Sorry to disturb you. We tried.

547
00:28:41.956 --> 00:28:43.525
In my experience.

548
00:28:43.592 --> 00:28:45.859
a wife knows more about her
husband's business than he does.

549
00:28:45.926 --> 00:28:48.495
Any idea
if Ernie has a relationship

550
00:28:48.563 --> 00:28:50.464
with Kayce Dutton?

551
00:28:50.532 --> 00:28:52.299
Everyone knows the white man

552
00:28:52.366 --> 00:28:54.835
who used to break horses
on the rez.

553
00:28:54.902 --> 00:28:57.438
That all? Nothing more personal?

554
00:28:57.505 --> 00:29:00.709
I never met him. but his wife
taught at Ernie's school.

555
00:29:00.774 --> 00:29:03.545
-Mm-hmm?
-He was quite fond of her.

556
00:29:03.612 --> 00:29:05.746
We both were.

557
00:29:06.548 --> 00:29:08.182
You don't say. ma'am.

558
00:29:08.983 --> 00:29:11.218
Do tell more.

559
00:29:14.888 --> 00:29:17.592
Lightning strikes
are getting close.

560
00:29:29.571 --> 00:29:31.805
Okay. come on.

561
00:29:32.840 --> 00:29:35.109
Come on. Back. back.

562
00:29:36.110 --> 00:29:37.478
Come on.

563
00:29:38.479 --> 00:29:39.847
Steady.

564
00:29:39.913 --> 00:29:41.750
How you doing?

565
00:29:41.815 --> 00:29:43.984
Don't focus on me.

566
00:29:46.220 --> 00:29:47.454
Come on.

567
00:30:01.335 --> 00:30:02.704
Come on.

568
00:30:21.955 --> 00:30:23.625
You good?

569
00:30:23.692 --> 00:30:24.958
-Throw us a line.
-Yeah!

570
00:30:26.994 --> 00:30:29.063
Our collar just used
our shotgun against us

571
00:30:29.129 --> 00:30:30.632
and beat feet into the woods.

572
00:30:30.699 --> 00:30:31.832
I'm-a pursue.

573
00:30:31.899 --> 00:30:33.901
And leave two men behind
this time?

574
00:30:43.812 --> 00:30:45.379
Come on.

575
00:30:51.786 --> 00:30:54.021
Sorry. sorry.

576
00:30:58.359 --> 00:30:59.627
All right.
you get him down the hill.

577
00:30:59.694 --> 00:31:01.328
I'm-a pursue that recluse.

578
00:31:01.395 --> 00:31:04.031
One is none. right?
Mission's not over.

579
00:31:04.098 --> 00:31:05.600
Please.

580
00:31:05.667 --> 00:31:07.702
I'm responsible for
a high enough body count today.

581
00:31:10.705 --> 00:31:12.272
All right. man.
let's get off this mountain

582
00:31:12.339 --> 00:31:14.341
before it throws
anything else at us.

583
00:31:14.408 --> 00:31:16.511
Come on. One. two. three.

584
00:31:20.682 --> 00:31:22.584
How was your field trip?

585
00:31:22.650 --> 00:31:24.084
It was enlightening.

586
00:31:24.151 --> 00:31:25.754
We learned that Dutton
killed the man

587
00:31:25.820 --> 00:31:28.790
who had tried to kill someone
important to his late wife.

588
00:31:28.857 --> 00:31:31.593
Meaning what. exactly?

589
00:31:31.659 --> 00:31:33.728
Well. Ernie and Monica Dutton
worked together.

590
00:31:33.795 --> 00:31:35.996
They grew so close that
he and his wife used to have

591
00:31:36.063 --> 00:31:39.500
Monica and her son over for
dinner when Kayce was deployed.

592
00:31:39.567 --> 00:31:41.001
We don't know if Kayce

593
00:31:41.068 --> 00:31:42.637
knew any of their history.

594
00:31:42.704 --> 00:31:44.739
Clegg just needs
to whisper that to the press.

595
00:31:44.806 --> 00:31:47.207
and they will have a field day
exploiting the Dutton name.

596
00:31:47.274 --> 00:31:50.310
Think anyone in this unit
will have a career after that?

597
00:31:50.377 --> 00:31:52.680
Now. I'm informing the Office
of Professional Responsibility

598
00:31:52.747 --> 00:31:55.048
-of the connection.
-You're feeding Kayce

599
00:31:55.115 --> 00:31:57.050
to the wolves
based off a theory.

600
00:31:57.117 --> 00:32:00.789
I'm keeping this team away
from his blast radius.

601
00:32:00.855 --> 00:32:04.291
You can file that under
"if you want a job done right."

602
00:32:10.565 --> 00:32:14.101
You can't pull a badge
over dots that may not connect.

603
00:32:14.903 --> 00:32:17.639
Government's the windshield.
rest of us are bugs.

604
00:32:20.207 --> 00:32:23.545
Okay. You were on
Kayce's six during the incident.

605
00:32:23.611 --> 00:32:27.481
So. walk us through it again.
from the start.

606
00:32:30.317 --> 00:32:32.754
We all pursued the Cleggs
to their hunting grounds.

607
00:32:32.821 --> 00:32:35.557
<i>Kayce and I broke off</i>
<i>from the team to outflank them.</i>

608
00:32:35.623 --> 00:32:36.791
<i>pushed up the hill.</i>

609
00:32:36.858 --> 00:32:39.627
Took fire from two positions?

610
00:32:40.427 --> 00:32:42.564
First.
we got separated by the I.E.D.

611
00:32:44.064 --> 00:32:45.600
<i>Wait. A decorated Navy SEAL</i>

612
00:32:45.667 --> 00:32:48.368
missed a trip wire?

613
00:32:49.169 --> 00:32:50.839
There's no chance.

614
00:32:50.905 --> 00:32:52.941
Maybe it was detonated

615
00:32:53.006 --> 00:32:54.374
remotely?

616
00:32:56.143 --> 00:32:57.879
Wes and Carson
were behind cover.

617
00:32:57.946 --> 00:32:59.714
They didn't have eyes on us yet.

618
00:33:06.353 --> 00:33:07.789
Avoided my worst nightmare

619
00:33:07.856 --> 00:33:09.289
thanks to you two.

620
00:33:09.356 --> 00:33:11.693
Lost track of how many times
you saved me today.

621
00:33:13.494 --> 00:33:15.797
Wish we could've
saved everyone. sir.

622
00:33:17.866 --> 00:33:19.366
Yeah.

623
00:33:29.844 --> 00:33:33.548
That's some U-turn you just
pulled on that transplant.

624
00:33:34.616 --> 00:33:36.918
Yeah. I might've
pegged him wrong.

625
00:33:36.985 --> 00:33:38.953
Yeah. Let's get back. man.
'cause I want to dig into

626
00:33:39.019 --> 00:33:40.387
that guy who almost
mudsucked us.

627
00:33:40.454 --> 00:33:42.824
Rather face off with that bear
than see Gifford.

628
00:33:42.891 --> 00:33:46.093
Yeah. I get it. but...
I ain't got no worries.

629
00:33:46.159 --> 00:33:47.762
You gonna be good on that front.

630
00:33:47.829 --> 00:33:50.632
It's the law of nature. right?

631
00:34:05.245 --> 00:34:06.681
Look. I'm sorry. Cal.

632
00:34:06.748 --> 00:34:09.416
Looks like Dutton's goose
is cooked.

633
00:34:09.483 --> 00:34:11.184
Oh. so you can prove that Clegg

634
00:34:11.251 --> 00:34:13.521
-was unarmed then. huh?
-Well. not exactly.

635
00:34:13.588 --> 00:34:15.389
But this office needs to project
a proactive stance

636
00:34:15.455 --> 00:34:16.824
against abuse of the badge.

637
00:34:16.891 --> 00:34:19.493
OPR has cleared the way
for you to fire Dutton

638
00:34:19.561 --> 00:34:21.261
before they finish their review.

639
00:34:21.328 --> 00:34:23.330
I warned you
hiring him was a mistake.

640
00:34:23.397 --> 00:34:24.899
Now you can correct that.

641
00:34:24.966 --> 00:34:28.903
You know. the last time
I ended a teammate's career.

642
00:34:28.970 --> 00:34:31.371
cost them everything. so...

643
00:34:31.438 --> 00:34:36.109
you want his badge so bad.
do it yourself.

644
00:34:37.045 --> 00:34:38.478
Check this out.

645
00:34:39.647 --> 00:34:42.149
We had the sheriff
search the scene again.

646
00:34:42.215 --> 00:34:43.618
looking for ways
the Cleggs might've had eyes

647
00:34:43.685 --> 00:34:46.521
on Kayce and Miles
while engaged in a gunfight.

648
00:34:46.588 --> 00:34:49.489
They found trail cams
from a grad student in Missoula

649
00:34:49.557 --> 00:34:52.560
studying gray-crowned
rosy finches.

650
00:34:52.627 --> 00:34:55.697
Did the sheriff miss the trail
cams in the initial processing?

651
00:34:55.763 --> 00:34:58.533
They're under-resourced
and looking for a missing gun.

652
00:34:58.600 --> 00:35:00.935
There was a node
on one of the cams.

653
00:35:01.002 --> 00:35:03.037
The Cleggs were piggybacking
off of it for hunting.

654
00:35:08.876 --> 00:35:10.812
That's Carson Clegg.

655
00:35:14.381 --> 00:35:17.217
Weapon firmly in hand.

656
00:35:24.826 --> 00:35:27.461
- How's that for thorough?
- "Abuse of the badge"

657
00:35:27.528 --> 00:35:31.766
looks pretty damn heroic
to me. Harry. Hmm?

658
00:35:32.767 --> 00:35:34.068
Glad you cleared this up.

659
00:35:34.134 --> 00:35:36.537
I'll tell OPR to shove it.

660
00:35:37.572 --> 00:35:39.306
Good work.

661
00:35:45.178 --> 00:35:46.748
Hey.

662
00:35:47.649 --> 00:35:50.918
It's true I'd rather be back
in D.C. than here.

663
00:35:50.985 --> 00:35:54.488
But not so much
that it turns me into a rat.

664
00:35:55.757 --> 00:35:58.492
Don't ever play me
like that again.

665
00:36:14.909 --> 00:36:18.746
Everybody. meet the man
who saved my life.

666
00:36:18.813 --> 00:36:19.914
Kayce Dutton.

667
00:36:23.985 --> 00:36:26.353
Figured a rancher needs his hat.

668
00:36:26.420 --> 00:36:30.290
Oh. this thing is filthy
and this room is sterile.

669
00:36:31.526 --> 00:36:34.529
That. uh. land out in Springhill
you were assaying?

670
00:36:35.596 --> 00:36:37.230
Belongs to the Quinns?

671
00:36:37.297 --> 00:36:38.866
It does.

672
00:36:39.667 --> 00:36:42.603
They went bust
overgrazing their pastures.

673
00:36:42.670 --> 00:36:44.138
It's gonna take
at least two seasons

674
00:36:44.204 --> 00:36:46.373
before it's fit
for cattle again.

675
00:36:48.442 --> 00:36:53.147
You saved my life
and my pocketbook today.

676
00:36:53.213 --> 00:36:55.149
I'm in your debt.

677
00:36:55.215 --> 00:36:57.752
Yeah. We all are.

678
00:36:58.686 --> 00:37:01.589
- Enjoy your family. sir.
- Now. hold-hold on.

679
00:37:03.390 --> 00:37:05.927
I need you out there
protecting Montanans

680
00:37:05.993 --> 00:37:08.930
without having to worry
about your ranch.

681
00:37:09.731 --> 00:37:11.331
Let me lend you some hands.

682
00:37:11.398 --> 00:37:13.433
Aw. I can't accept that.

683
00:37:13.500 --> 00:37:16.838
Hmm. When my father
makes you an offer.

684
00:37:16.904 --> 00:37:18.806
you don't have a choice.

685
00:37:18.873 --> 00:37:22.009
You had my back today. Kayce.

686
00:37:22.076 --> 00:37:24.812
It's only right I say thank you.

687
00:37:29.751 --> 00:37:31.686
You let Kayce know
he's in the clear. right?

688
00:37:31.753 --> 00:37:35.489
Mm-hmm. I left him a message.
but haven't heard back.

689
00:37:36.624 --> 00:37:38.391
I'm sure he doesn't think
our pack protected him today.

690
00:37:38.458 --> 00:37:41.294
Well. I get a sense
that he's used to others

691
00:37:41.361 --> 00:37:43.598
failing to stand up for him.

692
00:37:43.664 --> 00:37:45.600
Yeah. after digging
into his past.

693
00:37:45.666 --> 00:37:47.869
seems trouble's been
hunting Kayce his whole life.

694
00:37:47.935 --> 00:37:49.670
Yet he's still standing.

695
00:37:49.737 --> 00:37:53.174
Yeah. but it comes
at a hell of a price.

696
00:37:53.241 --> 00:37:54.642
- Look who it is.
- Oh.

697
00:37:54.709 --> 00:37:56.577
You beg me to come out
just so I can watch y'all

698
00:37:56.644 --> 00:37:58.513
cry in your beers?

699
00:37:59.312 --> 00:38:00.982
You saved my ass
with the Cleggs.

700
00:38:01.048 --> 00:38:02.449
I had no idea.

701
00:38:02.517 --> 00:38:04.719
Well. I had your back
just like you had mine.

702
00:38:04.786 --> 00:38:06.286
Well. the upside is.

703
00:38:06.353 --> 00:38:07.755
pretty sure we got Gifford
off your ass.

704
00:38:07.822 --> 00:38:09.857
Doubt that's the last time
I'll deal with him.

705
00:38:09.924 --> 00:38:11.759
- Or the Cleggs.
- Hey. check this out.

706
00:38:11.826 --> 00:38:14.262
I think we let
one of America's Most Wanted go.

707
00:38:14.327 --> 00:38:16.697
Specifically. Rudy Carpenter.

708
00:38:16.764 --> 00:38:19.366
Come on. Does that not
look like the eyes of the guy

709
00:38:19.432 --> 00:38:20.802
-who shot at us?
-"Serial bomber

710
00:38:20.868 --> 00:38:22.603
on the lam for three years"
Rudy Carpenter?

711
00:38:22.670 --> 00:38:24.672
Yeah. it would explain
why he was gunning for us.

712
00:38:24.739 --> 00:38:27.041
We can't
just ignore this. right?

713
00:38:30.144 --> 00:38:31.444
Oh. uh...

714
00:38:31.512 --> 00:38:33.047
Everybody. this is Dolly Weaver.

715
00:38:33.114 --> 00:38:35.116
Hi. I don't mean
to crash the party.

716
00:38:35.183 --> 00:38:37.317
but my father insisted

717
00:38:37.384 --> 00:38:39.053
on buying drinks
for the people who saved the job

718
00:38:39.120 --> 00:38:40.988
- of the man who saved his life.
- I'll drink to that.

719
00:38:41.055 --> 00:38:42.422
Hell yeah.

720
00:38:42.489 --> 00:38:44.625
Yes. thank you.

721
00:38:46.761 --> 00:38:48.563
Kayce.

722
00:38:48.629 --> 00:38:50.198
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

723
00:38:50.264 --> 00:38:51.331
Thanks to you.

724
00:38:51.398 --> 00:38:52.399
- Cheers.
- Yeah. All right.

725
00:38:52.465 --> 00:38:53.668
To your father.

726
00:38:53.734 --> 00:38:56.504
Thank you. Seriously.

727
00:38:59.140 --> 00:39:00.675
You know. for what it's worth.

728
00:39:00.741 --> 00:39:02.677
I hated turning your world
upside down.

729
00:39:02.743 --> 00:39:05.613
Nothing my dad despised more
than internal affairs.

730
00:39:05.680 --> 00:39:07.882
-We're all good.
-Oh. good day for you.

731
00:39:07.949 --> 00:39:10.017
You kept your badge
and you made a new friend.

732
00:39:10.084 --> 00:39:13.386
She's just grateful
we saved her dad.

733
00:39:13.453 --> 00:39:15.422
Oh. I know what grateful
looks like.

734
00:39:15.488 --> 00:39:17.325
and that is not
how she's eyeing you.

735
00:39:17.390 --> 00:39:19.327
Saddle up. cowboy.

736
00:39:23.297 --> 00:39:25.465
Okay. look. I have questions

737
00:39:25.533 --> 00:39:27.467
about how you two
arrived here together.

738
00:39:27.535 --> 00:39:31.672
but I'm just happy. man.
that you're here at all.

739
00:39:31.739 --> 00:39:34.407
Well. the fact that we can keep
that family's world

740
00:39:34.474 --> 00:39:38.746
from falling apart...
justified and right.

741
00:39:38.813 --> 00:39:40.047
Yeah.

742
00:39:40.114 --> 00:39:43.217
Well. maybe the badge
is a... a path to penance.

743
00:40:00.101 --> 00:40:02.737
Upset Dolly robbed you
of a chance to buy another round

744
00:40:02.803 --> 00:40:04.404
from your favorite bartender?

745
00:40:06.107 --> 00:40:07.942
Yeah.

746
00:40:08.009 --> 00:40:12.246
She seemed so scared not knowing
if her dad was dead or alive.

747
00:40:12.313 --> 00:40:13.614
Well. she's lucky to have

748
00:40:13.681 --> 00:40:15.249
that kind of relationship
with him.

749
00:40:18.953 --> 00:40:20.354
He's lucky. Yeah.

750
00:40:23.658 --> 00:40:25.393
Hmm.

751
00:40:25.458 --> 00:40:26.928
Bartender's my kid.

752
00:40:32.300 --> 00:40:34.168
Maddie.

753
00:40:34.235 --> 00:40:37.171
Been out of her life. uh.

754
